JOHANNESBURG - The Correctional Services Department says it’s investigating how 16 prisoners escaped from South Africa's biggest prison. WATCH: Sixteen prisoners escape from Sun City prison The department says it will not tolerate further security breaches. Correctional Services spokesperson Logan Maistry, said: “We have 243 correctional services across the country. 161,000 inmates the number of escaped prisoner moved from 1244 per annum to 50 per annum by 2017. Any security breach cannot be tolerated. One escape is one too many. This is receiving the highest priority.” eNCA